		<p>If bitcoin proves to be a useful medium of commerce, then the fact that early adopters get rich won&#8217;t matter.  If not, then the none of this matters.  If Dr. Evil sells his gigantic mass of bitcoins at some critical moment, the entire bitcoin project will collapse wiping out countless small bitcoin holders?  I guess it&#8217;s possible, sort of like if China decides to dump all its US bonds onto the market at once. But it only would matter for those who hold bitcoins as an investment; hopefully those folks  know that investment involves risk and have hefed their bets.  But ultimately bitcoin will only be important if it becomes a widely used medium of commerce, and if that happens Dr. Evil won&#8217;t matter.</p>

