				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://eoipsoblog.wordpress.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>vimothy</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.loper-os.org/?p=1009&amp;cpage=1#comment-7253">September 3, 2013 at 3:39 pm</a></div>

		<p>One obvious flaw in BitCoin&#8217;s design is that it is a virtual gold&#8211;that is to say, a commodity&#8211;rather than a virtual currency per se. If the price of currency drops dramatically, the issuing bank or central bank can contract the supply in order to stabilise the price. Enforcing this mechanism was, in fact, the aim of the gold standard. BitCoin possesses no such apparatus.</p>

