		<p>#2 will happen because there are certain markets which can ONLY and EXCLUSIVELY use Bitcoin for transactions (the Silk Road example is just one). </p>
<p>So long as Bitcoin serves a purpose that no other transactional system or currency can do, people will buy Bitcoin. </p>
<p>Someone wants to send $2 to a relative in China instantly? Only Bitcoin can do that. Want to perform a global trade in escrow with zero fees? Only Bitcoin can do that. Want to gamble a fraction of a penny on a game or play online poker in the US? Only Bitcoin can do that. </p>
<p>When Weimar&#8217;s currency hyperinflated, it had no use in any market. Bitcoin has uses regardless of price.</p>

