		<p>Dear cmccabe,</p>
<p>Most U.S. dollars might be in the hands of a business elite, but they at least conduct some useful commerce, and don&#8217;t act as a monolithic whole. The situation with Bitcoin is more analogous to a scenario where most U.S. dollars belong to a janitor working the night shift at the national mint. The Satoshi hoarders conduct no useful commerce or industry; they hold their coins purely by virtue of having mined when difficulty was very low. They add no value to the system, yet have in their hands a cheque that, were it cashed, would bleed a great many users who have invested actual wealth into Bitcoin exchanges.</p>
<p>Yours,<br />
-Stanislav</p>

