				<div id="div-comment-6756" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<cite class="fn">nope</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>

		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata"><a href="http://www.loper-os.org/?p=1009&amp;cpage=1#comment-6756">April 8, 2013 at 4:19 pm</a></div>

		<p>I won&#8217;t dream of convincing you you should prefer to own depreciating assets instead of appreciating assets; that would be silly.</p>
<p>What I would suggest, however, is that you consider the battery analogy more carefully: if inflation is meant to correspond to getting less energy back out of the battery than has been paid in, what, pray tell, would deflation correspond to?</p>

		<div class="reply">
		<a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='/?p=1009&#038;buffer_share=3c2a6&#038;replytocom=6756#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("div-comment-6756", "6756", "respond", "1009")'>Reply</a>		</div>
